    "The mathematical definitions are outlined in the next section for reproducibility and a high level overview is in Table 8.",
    "The detailed results of the spectral tasks is shown in Table 10.Normalized Root Mean Squared Error In our study, for observations (ground truth answers) {y i } n i=1 and predictions (generated outputs from the LLMs) {ŷ i } n i=1, the root mean squared error is defined asRMSE = 1 n n i=1 (y i -ŷi) 2 1/2.We consider two different types of normalizations.",
    "First, division by the empirical range of the target values,nRMSE range = RMSE max i y i -min i y i,and second, division by the sample standard deviation, Cross-Metric Correlation: Do different error metrics capture distinct failure modes in spectral reasoning?",
    "We compute correlations between the four error metrics averaged across tasks.",
    "The results show that nRMSE range, nRMSE std, and RelMAE are nearly perfectly correlated (ρ > 0.99), indicating that they are essentially redundant and capture the same failure mode."
